  "prompt": "Who is the best support hero in Dota 2?",
  "response": "Determining the \"best\" support hero in Dota 2 can be subjective and depends on various factors such as the current meta, team composition, and individual playstyle. However, some support heroes that are often regarded as strong picks due to their versatility, utility, and impact in games include:\n\n1. **Lion** - Offers great crowd control with his stun and hex, along with a powerful burst damage ultimate.\n2. **Shadow Shaman** - Provides solid lockdown, with the potential for pushing towers thanks to his ultimate ability, Serpent Wards.\n3. **Disruptor** - Great for controlling team fights and has valuable utility with his Ultimate, Static Storm.\n4. **Crystal Maiden** - Offers mana regeneration, crowd control, and scales well into the late game with her ultimate.\n5. **Enchantress** - Known for her healing and harassment capabilities, along with the ability to scale into a damage dealer.\n\nThe \"best\" hero may vary depending on patches and changes to the game, so it's always good to stay updated with the current meta and adapt to the needs of your team and opponents.",
